### Local config / secrets
# .claude/ holds two kinds of content: (a) user-local config + state
# (settings.local.json, scheduled_tasks.lock, worktrees/) which is
# per-clone and MUST be ignored, and (b) project-level Claude Code
# skills (.claude/skills/) which SHIP with the repo so every clone
# can invoke them. Git can't re-include children of an ignored
# parent directory, so list the specific (a) entries instead of the
# whole .claude/.
.claude/settings.local.json
.claude/scheduled_tasks.lock
.claude/worktrees/
.envrc
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local

### Defense-in-depth: common credential file patterns (pre-commit hooks
### also detect-private-key + detect-aws-credentials; this gitignores
### them before the hook even fires).
*.pem
*.key
*.p12
*.pfx
id_rsa*
id_ed25519*
id_ecdsa*
credentials.json
service-account*.json
.aws/
.gnupg/
.ssh/

