.pytest_cache/
# Local code-analysis tool cache (understand-anything) — per-machine, never commit.
# ~9.8M snapshot (knowledge-graph.json, fingerprints.json, meta.json) pinned to one
# developer's working tree at one instant; not a shared artifact. Directory-anchored
# trailing-slash form so it can only match this cache dir, never a tracked file.
.understand-anything/

### Coverage
coverage/
.coverage
htmlcov/
# The `coverage/` rule above is for test-coverage output dirs. The
# slice-041 BFF route `web/app/api/controls/[id]/coverage/` is a real
# source dir whose name collides with that rule. Git cannot re-include
# a path whose parent dir is excluded, so the negation is scoped to the
# `coverage` dir itself, then its contents. The `[id]` segment is a
# literal path component here, not a glob — escape the brackets.
!web/app/api/controls/\[id\]/coverage/
!web/app/api/controls/\[id\]/coverage/**

